org.opendaylight.controller.networkconfig.neutron

Interface INeutronSecurityRuleAware


  • public interface INeutronSecurityRuleAware
    This interface defines the methods required to be aware of Neutron Security Rules

    • Method Detail

      • canCreateNeutronSecurityRule

        int canCreateNeutronSecurityRule(NeutronSecurityRule securityRule)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified security rule can be created
        Parameters:
        securityRule - instance of proposed new Neutron Security Rule object
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the create operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.

      • neutronSecurityRuleCreated

        void neutronSecurityRuleCreated(NeutronSecurityRule securityRule)
        Services provide this interface method for taking action after a security rule has been created
        Parameters:
        securityRule - instance of new Neutron Security Rule object

      • canUpdateNeutronSecurityRule

        int canUpdateNeutronSecurityRule(NeutronSecurityRule delta,
                               NeutronSecurityRule original)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified security rule can be changed using the specified delta
        Parameters:
        delta - updates to the security rule object using patch semantics
        original - instance of the Neutron Security Rule object to be updated
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the update operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.

      • neutronSecurityRuleUpdated

        void neutronSecurityRuleUpdated(NeutronSecurityRule securityRule)
        Services provide this interface method for taking action after a security rule has been updated
        Parameters:
        securityRule - instance of modified Neutron Security Rule object

      • canDeleteNeutronSecurityRule

        int canDeleteNeutronSecurityRule(NeutronSecurityRule securityRule)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified security rule can be deleted
        Parameters:
        securityRule - instance of the Neutron Security Rule object to be deleted
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the delete operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.

        Parameters:
        securityRule - instance of deleted Neutron Security Rule object
